      "date": "2019-03-28 22:31:27.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\n> Trevis Autotest2 retesting enforced review-dne-zfs-part-1 session.\n > Requested by Alexander Zarochentsev because of LU-10632.\n >\n > Onyx Autotest retesting enforced review-dne-zfs-part-1 session.\n > Requested by Alexander Zarochentsev because of LU-11987.\n\nNote that even if there are multiple test failures for a *session* (in this case both recovery-small and sanity failed for \"review-dne-zfs-part-1\", the test *session* only needs to be restarted once.\n\nIf there are multiple different sessions failed, for example \"review-dne-zfs-part-1\" and \"review-ldiskfs\" then each one needs to be restarted separately with a proper LU ticket number.\n\n*NOTE* that \"review-ldiskfs-arm\" is an optional session and does *not* need to be retested unless there is some unusual failure that may relate to the patch.  There is a frequent failure with lnet-selftest on ARM, but sanity is passing regularly.",
